1.String.valueOf(j) - Converts a given int, boolean,char etc values to String// Multiple overloaded methods are present
                    under String class.
 Few methods for String class:                   
 append (), insert (), replace (), delete (), reverse (), capacity (), length (), deleteCharAt ()

if(reverse.contentEquals(input)) 
boolean java.lang.String.contentEquals(CharSequence cs)--Compares this string to the specified CharSequence

if(reverse.equalsIgnoreCase(input))
boolean java.lang.String.equalsIgnoreCase(String anotherString) -- Compares this String to another String,
ignoring case considerations.

if(reverse.equals(input))
boolean java.lang.String.equals(Object anObject)
Compares this string to the specified object. The result is true if and only if the argument is not null
and is a String object that represents the same sequence of characters as this object. 

Overrides: equals(...) in Object






 
